title: Adding new features for XRM v8.2
body:
There is a breaking change with the Control interface which may not be desirable. However, it seems to be required as Microsoft has changed things quite a bit with the latest XRM release (e.g. the introduction of the QuickForm control which does not support many of the methods that most other controls do).

## Adding new features for XRM v8.2
1. **Xrm.Page.ui**
   * Adding quickForms collection
   * Adding Xrm.Page.ui.QuickForm (https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/mt736908.aspx)
2. **Xrm.Async & XrmPromise**
   * Modifying the Async definitions to allow methods to return specific success or error callback delegates.
   * This is required because of new methods which return promises using callback delegates with different parameters (e.g. Xrm.Utility.openQuickCreate and Xrm.Mobile.offline methods)
3. **Xrm.Utility**
   * Modifying the Xrm.Utility.openQuickCreate method and related asynchronous promise methods (https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/jj602956.aspx#BKMK_openQuickCreate)
4. **Xrm.Page.data**
   * Adding Xrm.Page.data.save method with saveOptions (https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn481607.aspx#Anchor_2)
5. **Controls**
   * Moved methods from the Control interface into the StandardControl interface. This will be a breaking change, but is required because the Xrm.Page.ui.getControl methods can now return quick-form controls which support a smaller sub-set of methods than other controls.
   * Created UiLabelElement interface to controls which have labels which can be viewed and updated.
   * Created UiCanGetVisibleElement interface for controls which can have their current visibility level viewed (all form controls)
   * Created UiStandardElement interface for standard controls. This includes controls such as StandardControl, Tab and Section, but does not apply to the new quick form controls as they cannot have their visibility set.
   * Updated Control.getControlType method to use new type for ControlType with pre-defined string values.
   * Moving methods from AutoLookupControlinto UiKeyPressable interface as they are supported for both string and number controls (ref: https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/gg334266.aspx#Anchor_8)
   * Creating StringControl interface, extending the AutoLookupControl class to avoid breaking existing code.
   * Creating NumberControl interface.
6. **Attributes**
   * Updating the base Attribute interface to add getValue and setValue methods so that the attribute value can be accessed without casting to a data specific Attribute which is useful when the attribute type is not known. As per MSDN, all attributes have the getValue and setValue methods, but the return type depends on the attribute type (https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/gg334409.aspx#Anchor_15)
   * Modifying NumberAttribute, StringAttribute, DateAttribute, OptionSetAttribute, and LookupAttribute to return the relevant control collections (e.g. StringAttribute.controls returns Collection.ItemCollection<StringControl>)
   * Updated Attribute.getAttributeType and getFormat method to use new types AttributeType and AttributeFormat with pre-defined string values.
   * Updated getFormat method in DateAttribute, NumberAttribute, OptionSetAttributeFormat and StringAttribute to only return relevant values based on types for each attribute type (e.g. StringAttributeType).
7. **Xrm.Mobile.offline**
   * Adding new Xrm.Mobile.Offline (https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/mt787123.aspx)
8. **Xrm.Panel**
   * Adding new Xrm.Panel methods (https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/mt790281.aspx)
9. **Other**
   * Adding additional comments
   * Formatting changes to keep things consistent

title: Add extended AuthenticateOptions interface to passport-facebook
body:
This is useful since passing options with `authType` to passport's `authenticate` method fails since passport itself doesn't know about it. You can use this extended instead to retype it to the one that this method supports instead.

This fails:

```typescript
const authHandler = authenticate('facebook', {
    scope : ['email'],
    authType: 'rerequest',
    ...
});
```

with:

```
error TS2345: Argument of type '{ scope: string[]; authType: string; state: string; }' is not assignable to parameter of type 'AuthenticateOptions'.
Object literal may only specify known properties, and 'authType' does not exist in type 'AuthenticateOptions'.
```

This patch add an extended interface which can be used as follows:

```typescript
import { AuthenticateOptions } from 'passport-facebook';

const authHandler = authenticate('facebook', {
    scope : ['email'],
    authType: 'rerequest',
    ...
} as AuthenticateOptions);
```

To keep the backward compatibility with ES5, I think it is safe to rename the `WeakMap` declaration.

I know TS 2.2 is still in RC version now, but many people using it, including me :). So if you think this is too early and also bad idea then feel free to close this PR without merging it.

**Remaining failure** on `tsc` with TypeScript 2.0, caused by test file dependency on `jasmine`, which now uses TypeScript 2.1 `keyof`.
